```javascript
// These values should be replaced with your actual credentials and code
const clientId = 'your_client_id';
const redirectUri = 'your_redirect_uri';
const clientSecret = 'your_client_secret';
const code = 'your_received_authorization_code';

// URL endpoint for WordPress OAuth service
const oauthTokenUrl = 'https://public-api.wordpress.com/oauth2/token';

// Form data with the required parameters
const formData = new URLSearchParams();
formData.append('client_id', clientId);
formData.append('redirect_uri', redirectUri);
formData.append('client_secret', clientSecret);
formData.append('code', code);
formData.append('grant_type', 'authorization_code');

// POST request options
const requestOptions = {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded',
  },
  body: formData,
};

// Execute the POST request
fetch(oauthTokenUrl, requestOptions)
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => {
    console.log('Access Token:', data.access_token);
    // Perform further actions with the access token
  })
  .catch((error) => {
    console.error('Error fetching access token:', error);
  });
```
Keep in mind that if you're using Node.js, you'd need to use a package like `node-fetch` to make this code work, as the Fetch API is not natively available in Node.js environments.

Additionally, because handling `client_secret` on client-facing code (like in browsers) poses a security risk, the above code should only be executed in a secure server-side environment. Never expose sensitive credentials on the client side.

I have a custom CSS item: .fullScrCkeditor .ck-editor__editable {
	height: 600px;
} I want to dynamically change it's height. For example, when the component used this item is rendered I want it first check the dialog's height and then put the height in fullScrCkeditor as 65% of the dialog's height. How can I do this?

You can achieve this by dynamically setting the height of the `fullScrCkeditor` class based on the dialog's height using jQuery. Here's an example code snippet:

```javascript
// Get the height of the dialog
var dialogHeight = $(".dialog").height();

// Calculate 65% of the dialog's height
var newHeight = dialogHeight * 0.65;

// Set the new height for the .fullScrCkeditor class
$(".fullScrCkeditor .ck-editor__editable").css("height", newHeight + "px");
```

Make sure to replace `".dialog"` with the actual selector for your dialog element. By running this code when the component is rendered, it will dynamically adjust the height of the `.fullScrCkeditor` class based on the dialog's height.

