To navigate the user to a new screen with full details of a particular post, you can follow these steps:

1. Create a new screen component that will display the post details, for example, `PostDetails.js`.

2. In your `FutureMK` component, use the `useNavigation()` hook and the `onPress` prop of the `<Pressable>` component to navigate to the `PostDetails` screen and pass the full `mkData` as a parameter.

3. In your `PostDetails` screen, use the `route` prop to access the passed `mkData` and display the full details of the post.

Here's an example of how to implement these steps:

1. Create `PostDetails.js`:

```javascript
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text } from 'react-native';
import { gStyle } from '../styles/style';

const PostDetails = ({ route }) => {
  const { mkData } = route.params;

  return (
    <View style={gStyle.main}>
      <Text style={gStyle.dateFutureMK}>
        {moment(mkData.time.toDate()).format('Do MMM YYYY')}
