       const source = { uri: response.uri };
       // do something with the source object (e.g. set imageData hook)
     }
   });
   ```

   Note that the response object returned by `showImagePicker` contains a `uri` property that you can use to show the selected image.

3. Verify that you have installed `react-native-image-picker` properly, including all required dependencies. Follow the installation instructions for the library carefully to ensure everything is set up correctly.

If none of these solutions work, you can also try updating your `react-native-image-picker` library or even your React Native version itself. Check the library's documentation to see if there are any issues with the version you are using and if there are any compatibility issues with your current React Native version.

